'''Daisy Bopanna'''(born 4 December 1982) is an [[India]]n [[actress]] who appears primarily in [[Cinema of Karnataka|Kannada cinema]]. She has worked with actors like [[Upendra (actor)|Upendra]] in ''[[Aishwarya (film)|Aishwarya]]'', [[Kamal Hassan]] in ''[[Rama Shama Bhama]]'' and [[Akshay Kumar]] in ''[[Garam Masala (2005 film)|Garam Masala]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Daisy Bopanna biography |url=http://www.apunkachoice.com/celebrities/daisy_bopanna |publisher=apunkachoice.com |accessdate=15 May 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110624052926/http://www.apunkachoice.com/celebrities/daisy_bopanna/ |archivedate=24 June 2011 |df=dmy }}</ref>
==Personal life== Bopanna's family hails from [[Kodagu]] (also known by its Anglicised former name of Coorg). She was born on 4 December 1982. Daisy did her schooling from Aurobindo School,<ref name="sify">{{cite news|title=Daisy Bopanna interview|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/kannada/interview.php?id=13916749&cid=2404|publisher=sify.com|accessdate=15 May 2011}}</ref> pre-university at Kumarans College and graduated with a [[Bachelor of Fine Arts]] degree from [[Chitrakala Parishat]] in [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]]. She is married to Amit Jaju, a partner with the forensic practice of Ernst & Young and son of Prakash Jaju.<ref>{{cite news |title= Daisy Bopanna gets hitched |url= http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-06-01/news-interviews/29608151_1_daisy-bopanna-kannada-films-actress |publisher= ''The Times of India'' |date= 1 June 2011}}</ref> Her brother is an eminent advertising professional working in Mumbai.
==Career==
She started with theater, working for a short time with B. Jayasri's Spandana theatre camp and also contemporary English theatre<ref name="sify" /> with Preetam Koilpillai, and never looked back. Her first movie ''Bimba'' (The Image) was sent to the prestigious Berlin & Frankfurt Film Festival, winning international awards. The movie, directed by [[Kavitha Lankesh]], explored the exploitation of child artistes in the film industry. Her later work in ''Bhagavan'' with [[Darshan (actor)|Darshan]] earned her the tag of "Spicy Daisy".<ref name="hindu">{{cite news|title=Daisy Bopanna interview|url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2008/07/14/stories/2008071450500100.htm|publisher=The Hindu|accessdate=15 May 2011|location=Chennai, India|date=14 July 2008}}</ref>
After that Daisy went on to act in many films such as ''Rama Shyama Bhama'', ''Thavarina Siri'', ''Aishwarya'', ''Satyavaan Savitri'', ''Gaalipata'', ''Olave Jeevana Lekkachara'', ''Crazy Loka'' and other films. Daisy proved that she is a good performer in all these films. Daisy event went on to act in Hindi films like ''Garam Masala'', where she was seen opposite [[Akshay Kumar]] and [[John Abraham (actor)|John Abraham]]. Though the film was a hit, Daisy had to wait for another two years to find herself a next project. The next project came in the form of ''United Six'', which was average at the box office.{{citation needed|date=August 2013}}
She starred in more than 150 regional ads before being cast in the Priyadarshan movie ''[[Garam Masala (2005 film)|Garam Masala]]''. She has also starred in a Tamil and Telugu film, opposite leading stars like [[Kamal Hassan]],[[Ravi Teja]] and Ganesh. Her first ad film was with veteran ad film maker [[Rajiv Menon]].{{citation needed|date=August 2013}}
