'''Dan Wédo''' is a loa of the waters in the form of a great [[Serpent (symbolism)|serpent]] in [[Haitian Vodou|Vodou]].

He is syncretized with the image of [[Louis IX of France|St. Louis IX]], a King of [[France]] (1226-1270) who died of disease while on crusade. St. Louis is usually depicted in armor and crowned.

